International Conference on Spatial Analysis and GEOmatics
=AB Geomatic Methods, Models and Knowledge
for Land Planning and Landscape Management =BB

http://sageo10.univ-toulouse.fr/

17-19 Novembre 2010 =E0 Toulouse (France)

=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D
SAGEO is the rope which ties the different fields, approaches,=20
disciplines and actors, promoting the geoinformatics. Annual=20
international conference organized by the GdR MAGIS and the European=20
Research Group S4, SAGEO aims to :
- present recent research in the fields of geoinformatics, spatial=20
analysis and Geographic Information;
- gather communities of researchers from various disciplines;
- foster relations between specialists developing and enhancing research=20
in government agencies, businesses and local authorities;
- provide an information and exchange place on research and development=20
of geographic information in general, at national and international.

=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D
Important Dates
----------------------
April 2010 : call of papers
- June 15th 2010 : papers and posters submission
- September 15th 2010 : notification of acceptance to authors
- October 15th 2010 : final submission of revised papers
- November 17th-19th 2010 : conference

=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
