Aims and scope
--------------------
The main theme for SAGeO 2010 is :
Geomatic Methods, Models and Knowledge for Land Planning and Landscape=20
Management.

Contributions should preferably concern this topic, and more widely:

1/Concerning tools, methods and models:
- Complex systems, modeling and spatio-temporal simulation
- Integration, fusion, multi-scale and automatic generalization
- Spatial Data Infrastructure, interoperability, metadata, ontologies
- Databases and knowledge bases, knowledge representation, knowledge=20
engineering
- Prospective simulation models, validation and generalization, models=20
coupling
- Modeling and management of uncertainty, error propagation, sensitivity=20
analysis
- Spatial datamining, spatial analysis, geostatistics
- Spatial cognition: perception and appropriation of space
- Geo-visualization, Webmapping, dynamic mapping, mobile applications,=20
Web services and Semantic Web, Networks, Ubiquitous GIS
- Spatial data structure and geometric algorithms, modeling of spatial=20
relations, graph analysis, trajectory analysis
- Remote sensing and image processing, segmentation, pixel=20
classification and object, time series processing, LiDAR, multi-source=20
classification, sensors
- Uses and socio-economic impacts of geographic information (legal,=20
economic, networks of actors).
- Decision support techniques.

2/Concerning thematic fields:
- Landscape ecology, environment, natural resources management
- Land management and territorial prospective
- Representations and urban dynamics
- Coastal management, seashore
- Change of occupation and land use
- Transports, flux and mobilities
- Risks
- Decision support, territorial governance
- Actors and representation, conflicts of use
- Collaboration, participation, mediation, companion modelling
- Teaching geoinformatics and spatial analysis

=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D
Paper Submission
------------------------
Three types of propositions are possible to submit:
- Scientific articles (12 to 15 pages, about 5000 words) for oral=20
presentation and publication in the electronic proceedings of the SaG=E9o=
=20
2010 conference ;
- posters accompanied by a short text (2 to 3 pages including title,=20
abstract and keywords) to be exposed during the conference ;
- oral presentations of R & D in Geomatics implemented by private=20
companies, consulting firms and local authorities, etc.. (synthetically=20
described in a page by title, abstract and keywords).
Texts will be written in french or english and must follow those=20
guidelines :
http://www.hermes-science.fr/fr/cons_actes.html
Submission website : http://sageo10.univ-toulouse.fr/openconf
Best papers will be selected for a collective proposition of a special=20
issue to the "European Journal of GIS and Spatial Analysis", the "Revue=20
d'Ing=E9nierie des Syst=E8mes d'Information (ISI)" and "Annals of GIS"
IMPORTANT : All accepted paper requires registration and the presence of=20
at least one of the authors.

